  "course_description": "For first-year students only. Entry level seminar focusing on a specific topic.",
  "course_notes": "(Freshmen Seminar - Limited to First Year Students Only) (Gender, Sex, and Science Fiction: How can science fiction help us understand the limitations and possibilities of sex and gender? When we dream of different futures, what forms does gender take in those futures? Reading science fiction, African and Afro futurism, and speculative fiction, and viewing some television and film selections, our course explores the ways in which science fiction can reveal how we understand gender and society. Introducing concepts from feminist science studies, we will examine the intertwining of gender, sex, race, and technology.)",
